org.transitime.db.structs

Class StopPath

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.transitime.db.structs.StopPath
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, org.hibernate.classic.Lifecycle

    @Entity
public class StopPath
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable, org.hibernate.classic.Lifecycle
    A StopPath is a set of points that defines how a vehicle gets from one stop to another. The stops do not necessarily lie directly on the segments since the segments are likely to be street center line data while the stops are usually on the sidewalk.
    Author:
    SkiBu Smith
    See Also:
